== Scholarly projects == In an effort to understand postcolonialism through scholarship and technology, in addition to important literature, many stakeholders have published projects about the subject. Here is an incomplete list of projects.
* [https://scalar.chass.ncsu.edu/bodies-and-structures/index Bodies and Structure] (2019), on the spatial history of [[Japan]] and its empire *[http://chicanadiasporic.org/journey/chicana/index?path=index Chicana Diasporic] (2018), a research hub that highlights the [[Chicana feminism|Chicana]] Caucus of the [[National Women's Political Caucus|National Women's Caucus]] from 1973–1979 *[http://harlemshadows.org/ Harlem Shadows] (2018), an open source collection of [[Claude McKay]]'s 1922 collection of poems * [http://passamaquoddypeople.com/ Passamaquoddy People: At Home on the Oceans and Lakes] (2014), a digital archive of photos and recordings of the [[Passamaquoddy|Passamaquaddy]] people * [https://writersmakeworlds.com/ Postcolonial Writers Make Worlds] (2017), critical reading of [[Black British|Black]] and [[British Asian|Asian British]] literature * [http://xpmethod.plaintext.in/torn-apart/volume/2/index Torn Apart/Separados] (2018), visualizations and scholarly journal tracking global crisis situations * W.E.B. Du Bois's Data Portraits: Visualizing Black America (2019), charts from [[W. E. B. Du Bois|W.E.B. Du Bois]] in color about the lives of [[African Americans|Black Americans]]
